  "description": "When to pay tax or National Insurance on tests for COVID-19 and personal protective equipment (PPE).",
  "details": {
    "body": "<p>As an employer providing COVID-19 tests and equipment, you have certain tax, National Insurance and reporting obligations.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"covid-19-tests\">COVID-19 tests</h2>\n\n<p>You do not have to pay tax or National Insurance on diagnostic tests for COVID-19 if:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>your employees pay for tests and you pay them back</li>\n  <li>you provide tests for your employees directly</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div role=\"note\" aria-label=\"Information\" class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Healthcare workers may also be able to <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.nhs.uk/nhs-services/covid-19-services/testing-for-covid-19/who-can-get-a-free-covid-19-rapid-lateral-flow-test/\">get a test through the free NHS programme</a>.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2 id=\"personal-protective-equipment-ppe\">Personal protective equipment (PPE)</h2>\n\n<p>You must <a href=\"/government/collections/coronavirus-covid-19-personal-protective-equipment-ppe\">provide your employees with personal protective equipment</a> free of charge if your risk assessment shows that PPE is needed in their role.</p>\n\n<p>If the employee has to buy their own PPE because you cannot provide it, you must reimburse them for it.</p>\n\n<p>You do not have to pay tax or National Insurance if you provide your employees with PPE or reimburse them for the cost of buying their own.</p>\n\n<p>If you do not reimburse the cost, your employee cannot claim tax relief on the expense.</p>\n",
    "external_related_links": [

    ]
  },
